licate\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"This issue or pull request already exists\\\",\\\"node_id\\\":\\\"LA_kwDOTM7tpM8AAAACqDKfLw\\\"},{\\\"name\\\":\\\"area:core\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"node_id\\\":\\\"LA_kwDOTM7tpM8AAAACqDKgUQ\\\"},{\\\"name\\\":\\\"platform:macos\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"node_id\\\":\\\"LA_kwDOTM7tpM8AAAACqDKgiA\\\"},{\\\"name\\\":\\\"area:api\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"node_id\\\":\\\"LA_kwDOTM7tpM8AAAACqDKgiQ\\\"}],\\\"comments\\\":1,\\\"created_at\\\":\\\"2026-07-03T19:51:16Z\\\",\\\"updated_at\\\":\\\"2026-07-03T19:51:18Z\\\"},{\\\"id\\\":4805979424,\\\"number\\\":23,\\\"state\\\":\\\"CLOSED\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"[Documentation] Claude Code release notes for v1.0.71 is not informative. Need more detailed notes.\\\",\\\"body\\\":\\\"The release notes for Claude Code v1.0.71 is as follows: \\\\n\\\\n\\\\u003e Version 1.0.71:\\\\n\\\\u003e      • Background commands: (Ctrl-b) to run any Bash command in the background so Claude can keep working (great for dev servers, tailing logs, etc.)\\\\n\\\\u003e      • Customizable status line: add your terminal prompt to Claude Code with /statusline\\\\n\\\\nI couldn't understand what `/statusline` would do. I asked Claude Code and it provided this useful information. \\\\n\\\\n\\\\u003e The /statusline command customizes the status bar at the bottom of your Claude Code interface. It lets you display useful information like:\\\\n\\\\u003e \\\\n\\\\u003e   - Current working directory\\\\n\\\\u003e   - Git branch and status\\\\n\\\\u003e   - Active model (Claude 3.5 Sonnet, Opus, etc.)\\\\n\\\\u003e   - Project context\\\\n\\\\u003e   - Custom text or emojis\\\\n\\\\u003e   - System info (time, date, etc.)\\\\n\\\\u003e \\\\n\\\\u003e   Think of it like customizing your terminal prompt (PS1), but for Claude Code's interface. You can configure what information appears and how it's formatted.\\\\n\\\\u003e \\\\n\\\\u003e   For example, a statusLine might show:\\\\n\\\\u003e   📁 /Users/XXXX/YYYY/Sample.API | 🌿 Test/sample-features | 🤖 Opus 4.1\\\\n\\\\nIt would be really helpful to have an abridged version of the information (in block quotes) as part of the release notes.\\\",\\\"user\\\":{\\\"login\\\":\\\"mangowhoiscloud\\\"},\\\"labels\\\":[{\\\"name\\\":\\\"documentation\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"Improvements or additions to documentation\\\",\\\"node_id\\\":\\\"LA_kwDOTM7tpM8AAAACqDKfKA\\\"},{\\\"name\\\":\\\"enhancement\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"New feature or request\\\",\\\"node_id\\\":\\\"LA_kwDOTM7tpM8AAAACqDKfNg\\\"}],\\\"comments\\\":1,\\\"created_at\\\":\\\"2026-07-03T19:51:13Z\\\",\\\"updated_at\\\":\\\"2026-07-03T19:51:15Z\\\"},{\\\"id\\\":4805979301,\\\"number\\\":22,\\\"state\\\":\\\"CLOSED\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"[BUG] Search/Grep tool is BROKEN\\\",\\\"body\\\":\\\"E.g. I have a file in api_server/autogen_executor.py and I confirmed CC is in the root of the repo where that folder + file is.  I also do have the pattern filename_patterns in that file.\\\\n\\\\nYet I get:\\\\n\\\\n```\\\\n? You're absolutely right. Let me search for the actual _get_file_name_from_content function to understand its structure and placement, then create a similar function in the same location.\\\\n\\\\n? Search(pattern: \\\\\\\"filename_patterns\\\\\\\", output_mode: \\\\\\\"content\\\\\\\")\\\\n  ?  Found 0 lines \\\\n\\\\n? Search(pattern: \\\\\\\"self\\\\\\\\.filename_patterns\\\\\\\", output_mode: \\\\\\\"content\\\\\\\")\\\\n  ?  Found 0 lines \\\\n\\\\n? Search(pattern: \\\\\\\"_get_file_name_from_content\\\\\\\", output_mode: \\\\\\\"content\\\\\\\")\\\\n  ?  Found 0 lines \\\\n\\\\n? Search(pattern: \\\\\\\"get_file_name.*from.*content\\\\\\\", output_mode: \\\\\\\"content\\\\\\\")\\\\n  ?  Found 0 lines \\\\n\\\\n? Let me search for patterns that look at the start of file:\\\\n\\\\n? Search(pattern: \\\\\\\"start.*file\\\\\\\", output_mode: \\\\\\\"content\\\\\\\", head_limit: 10)\\\\n  ?  Found 0 lines \\\\n\\\\n? PostToolUse:Grep hook execution cancelled\\\\n\\\\n\\\\u003e Where are you located? What is your current working dir and where are you searching?\\\\n\\\\n? Bash(pwd)\\\\n  ?  /home/jon/h2ogpt_internal\\\\n  ?  Interrupted by user\\\\n\\\\n\\\\u003e Why is your search failing, it's simply in api_server/autogen_executor.py -- Don't just continue, explain what is going on with your searches.\\\\n\\\\n? You're absolutely right - my searches were failing because I was searching the entire codebase rather than focusing on the specific file you mentioned. Let me check that file directly:\\\\n\\\\n? Read(api_server/autogen_executor.py)\\\\n  ?  Read 1784 lines (ctrl+r to expand)\\\\n\\\\n? Now I can see the _get_file_name_from_content function! It's at line 544. Let me look at that function more closely:\\\\n\\\\n? Read(api_server/autogen_executor.py)\\\\n  ?  Read 30 lines (ctrl+r to expand)\\\\n  ?  Interrupted by user\\\\n\\\\n\\\\u003e No no, if you search in entire code base you should be finding it\\\\n\\\\n? You're right, let me search the entire codebase properly for the _get_file_name_from_content function:\\\\n\\\\n? Bash(find . -name \\\\\\\"*.py\\\\\\\" -exec grep -l \\\\\\\"_get_file_name_from_content\\\\\\\" {} \\\\\\\\;)\\\\n  ?  Interrupted by user\\\\n\\\\n\\\\u003e No, go back to Search(pattern: \\\\\\\"_get_file_name_from_content\\\\\\\", output_mode: \\\\\\\"content\\\\\\\") failing to find the right thing?\\\\n\\\\n? You're absolutely right - my Grep search should have found it. Let me try the Grep tool again:\\\\n\\\\n? Search(pattern: \\\\\\\"_get_file_name_from_content\\\\\\\", output_mode: \\\\\\\"content\\\\\\\")\\\\n  ?  Found 0 lines \\\\n\\\\n? That's strange - the Grep tool is not finding matches that the bash find command clearly found. Let me try a simpler pattern:\\\\n\\\\n? Search(pattern: \\\\\\\"get_file_name_from_content\\\\\\\", output_mode: \\\\\\\"content\\\\\\\")\\\\n  ?  Found 0 lines \\\\n\\\\n? The Grep tool seems to be having issues finding patterns that clearly exist. This explains why my earlier searches failed - there appears to be a problem with the Grep tool's search functionality. The bash find command successfully found the files containing\\\\n  _get_file_name_from_content in:\\\\n\\\\n  1. ./api_server/test_autogen_utils.py\\\\n  2. ./api_server/autogen_executor.py\\\\n\\\\n\\\\n```\\\",\\\"user\\\":{\\\"login\\\":\\\"mangowhoiscloud\\\"},\\\"labels\\\":[{\\\"name\\\":\\\"bug\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"Something isn't working\\\",\\\"node_id\\\":\\\"LA_kwDOTM7tpM8AAAACqDKfIg\\\"},{\\\"name\\\":\\\"has repro\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"node_id\\\":\\\"LA_kwDOTM7tpM8AAAACqDKgTw\\\"},{\\\"name\\\":\\\"area:tools\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"node_id\\\":\\\"LA_kwDOTM7tpM8AAAACqDKg_w\\\"}],\\\"comments\\\":1,\\\"created_at\\\":\\\"2026-07-03T19:51:12Z\\\",\\\"updated_at\\\":\\\"2026-07-03T19:51:13Z\\\"},{\\\"id\\\":4805979154,\\\"number\\\":21,\\\"state\\\":\\\"CLOSED\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"Invalid JSON Encoding Error During API Request\\\",\\\"body\\\":\\\"**Bug Description**\\\\nGetting a 400 error from the API mid-edit: API Error: 400 {\\\\\\\"type\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"error\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"error\\\\\\\":{\\\\\\\"type\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"invalid_request_error\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"message\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"The request body is not valid JSON: no low surrogate in string: line 1 column \\\\n     232122 (char 232121)\\\\\\\"}}\\\\n\\\\n**Environment Info**\\\\n- Platform: darwin\\\\n- Terminal: Apple_Terminal\\\\n- Version: 1.0.72\\\\n- Feedback ID: bc0a674b-a250-4923-940a-34fff521408e\\\\n\\\\n**Errors**\\\\n```json\\\\n[{\\\\\\\"error\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"Error: 400 {\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"type\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"error\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"error\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":{\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"type\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"invalid_request_error\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"message\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"The request body is not valid JSON: no low surrogate in string: line 1 column 232122 